#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np23"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:0.5"
msgid "23. Bhesajjasikkhāpada"
msgstr "23. The training rule on tonics"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np23.1.1, pts-vp-en2.126, ms1V_2307
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa "
"ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā pilindavaccho rājagahe pabbhāraṃ sodhāpeti "
"leṇaṃ kattukāmo."
msgstr ""
"At that time Venerable Pilindavaccha, wanting to build a shelter, was having "
"a hillside cleared near Rājagaha."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro yenāyasmā pilindavaccho tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"On that occasion King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha went to Pilindavaccha,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ pilindavacchaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmantaṃ "
"pilindavacchaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.6"
msgid "“kiṃ, bhante, thero kārāpetī”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, what are you having made?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.7"
msgid "“Pabbhāraṃ, mahārāja, sodhāpemi leṇaṃ kattukāmo”ti."
msgstr ""
"“I’m clearing the hillside, great king, because I want to build a shelter.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.8"
msgid "“Attho, bhante, ayyassa ārāmikenā”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you need a monastery worker?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.9"
msgid "“Na kho, mahārāja, bhagavatā ārāmiko anuññāto”ti."
msgstr "“The Master hasn’t allowed monastery workers.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.10"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhante, bhagavantaṃ paṭipucchitvā mama āroceyyāthā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Venerable, please ask the Master and tell me the outcome.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.11"
msgid ""
"“Evaṃ, mahārājā”ti kho āyasmā pilindavaccho rañño māgadhassa seniyassa "
"bimbisārassa paccassosi."
msgstr "“Yes, great king.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.12"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi."
msgstr ""
"And Pilindavaccha instructed, inspired, and gladdened King Bimbisāra with a "
"teaching,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.13"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmatā pilindavacchena dhammiyā "
"kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā "
"āyasmantaṃ pilindavacchaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"after which the king rose from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated "
"Pilindavaccha with his right side towards him, and departed."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli3.249, ms1V_2308
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.14"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho bhagavato santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards Pilindavaccha sent a message to the Master:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.15"
msgid "“rājā, bhante, māgadho seniyo bimbisāro ārāmikaṃ dātukāmo."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable Sir, King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha wishes to provide a "
"monastery worker."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.127
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.16"
msgid "Kathaṃ nu kho, bhante, mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?"
msgstr "What should I do?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā "
"bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "The Master then gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. HTML: <span class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.18"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ārāmikan”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow monastery workers.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.19"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro yenāyasmā pilindavaccho "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Once again King Bimbisāra went to Pilindavaccha,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.20"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ pilindavacchaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, sat down,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.21"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmantaṃ "
"pilindavacchaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.22"
msgid "“anuññāto, bhante, bhagavatā ārāmiko”ti?"
msgstr "“Venerable, has the Master allowed monastery workers?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.23"
msgid "“Evaṃ, mahārājā”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, great king.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.24"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhante, ayyassa ārāmikaṃ dammī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, I’ll provide you with a monastery worker.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.25"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro āyasmato pilindavacchassa ārāmikaṃ "
"paṭissuṇitvā vissaritvā cirena satiṃ paṭilabhitvā aññataraṃ sabbatthakaṃ "
"mahāmattaṃ āmantesi—"
msgstr ""
"But after making this promise, he forgot, and only remembered after a long "
"time. He then addressed the official in charge of all practical affairs,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.26"
msgid "“yo mayā, bhaṇe, ayyassa ārāmiko paṭissuto, dinno so ārāmiko”ti?"
msgstr "“Listen, has the monastery worker I promised been provided?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.27"
msgid "“Na kho, deva, ayyassa ārāmiko dinno”ti."
msgstr "“No, sir, he hasn’t.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.28"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ nu kho, bhaṇe, ito hi taṃ hotī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long is it since we made that promise?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: gaṇetvā → vigaṇetvā (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.29"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so mahāmatto rattiyo gaṇetvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ "
"etadavoca—"
msgstr "The official counted the days and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.30"
msgid "“pañca, deva, rattisatānī”ti."
msgstr "“It’s five hundred days.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.31"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhaṇe, ayyassa pañca ārāmikasatāni dehī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, provide him with five hundred monastery workers.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.32"
msgid "“Evaṃ, devā”ti"
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: pādāsi → adāsi (s1-3)
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.128,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.33"
msgid ""
"kho so mahāmatto rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa paṭissuṇitvā "
"āyasmato pilindavacchassa pañca ārāmikasatāni pādāsi, pāṭiyekko gāmo nivisi."
msgstr ""
"The official provided Pilindavaccha with five hundred monastery workers and "
"a separate village was established."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.1.34"
msgid "Ārāmikagāmakotipi naṃ āhaṃsu, pilindagāmakotipi naṃ āhaṃsu."
msgstr "They called it “The Monastery Workers’ Village” and “Pilinda Village.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli3.250, pts-cs-bu-np23.1.2, ms1V_2309
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā pilindavaccho tasmiṃ gāmake kulūpako hoti."
msgstr "And Pilindavaccha began associating with the families in that village."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ ādāya "
"pilindagāmakaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"One morning he robed up, took his bowl and robe, and entered Pilinda Village "
"for almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena tasmiṃ gāmake ussavo hoti."
msgstr "At that time they were holding a festival in that village"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.4"
msgid "Dārakā alaṅkatā mālākitā kīḷanti."
msgstr "and the children were dressed up with ornaments and garlands."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho pilindagāmake sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena "
"aññatarassa ārāmikassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"As Pilindavaccha was walking on continuous almsround, he came to the house "
"of a certain monastery worker,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.6"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "where he sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.7"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena tassā ārāmikiniyā dhītā aññe dārake alaṅkate mālākite "
"passitvā rodati—"
msgstr ""
"Just then the daughter of the house had seen the other children dressed up "
"in ornaments and garlands, and she cried,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.8"
msgid "“mālaṃ me detha,"
msgstr "“Give me a garland!"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.9"
msgid "alaṅkāraṃ me dethā”ti."
msgstr "Give me ornaments!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.10"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho taṃ ārāmikiniṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "Pilindavaccha asked her mother"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.11"
msgid "“kissāyaṃ dārikā rodatī”ti?"
msgstr "why the girl was crying."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.12"
msgid "“Ayaṃ, bhante, dārikā aññe dārake alaṅkate mālākite passitvā rodati—"
msgstr "She told him, adding,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.13"
msgid "‘mālaṃ me detha, alaṅkāraṃ me dethā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.14"
msgid "Kuto amhākaṃ duggatānaṃ mālā kuto, alaṅkāro”ti?"
msgstr "“How can poor people like us afford garlands and ornaments?”"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.129
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho aññataraṃ tiṇaṇḍupakaṃ gahetvā taṃ ārāmikiniṃ "
"etadavoca—"
msgstr "Pilindavaccha took a roll of grass and said to the mother,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.16"
msgid "“handimaṃ tiṇaṇḍupakaṃ tassā dārikāya sīse paṭimuñcā”ti."
msgstr "“Here, place this pad of grass on the girl’s head.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.17"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sā ārāmikinī taṃ tiṇaṇḍupakaṃ gahetvā tassā dārikāya sīse paṭimuñci."
msgstr "She did,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.18"
msgid "Sā ahosi suvaṇṇamālā abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr "and it turned into a beautiful golden garland."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.19"
msgid "Natthi tādisā raññopi antepure suvaṇṇamālā."
msgstr "Even the royal compound had nothing like it."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.20"
msgid "Manussā rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ārocesuṃ—"
msgstr "People told King Bimbisāra,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.21"
msgid ""
"“amukassa, deva, ārāmikassa ghare suvaṇṇamālā abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, in the house of a particular monastery worker there’s a beautiful "
"golden garland."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.22"
msgid "Natthi tādisā devassāpi antepure suvaṇṇamālā."
msgstr "Even in your household, sir, there’s nothing like it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.23"
msgid "Kuto tassa duggatassa."
msgstr "So how did those poor people get it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.24"
msgid "Nissaṃsayaṃ corikāya ābhatā”ti."
msgstr "No doubt it was taken by theft.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.25"
msgid "Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro taṃ ārāmikakulaṃ bandhāpesi."
msgstr "And King Bimbisāra had that family imprisoned."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.26"
msgid ""
"Dutiyampi kho āyasmā pilindavaccho pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaraṃ "
"ādāya pilindagāmakaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Once again Pilindavaccha robed up in the morning, took his bowl and robe, "
"and entered Pilinda Village for almsfood."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.27"
msgid ""
"Pilindagāmake sapadānaṃ piṇḍāya caramāno yena tassa ārāmikassa nivesanaṃ "
"tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr ""
"As he was walking on continuous almsround, he came to the house of that "
"monastery worker."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.28"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paṭivissake pucchi—"
msgstr "And he asked the neighbors,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.29"
msgid "“kahaṃ imaṃ ārāmikakulaṃ gatan”ti?"
msgstr "“Where is the family of this monastery worker?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.2.30"
msgid "“Etissā, bhante, suvaṇṇamālāya kāraṇā raññā bandhāpitan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, the king had them imprisoned because of that golden garland.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-np23.1.3, ms1V_2310
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho yena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa "
"nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Pilindavaccha then went to King Bimbisāra’s house"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.2"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "and sat down on a prepared seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro yenāyasmā pilindavaccho tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "King Bimbisāra approached Pilindavaccha,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.4"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ pilindavacchaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "bowed, and sat down."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.130
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.5"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ āyasmā "
"pilindavaccho etadavoca—"
msgstr "And Pilindavaccha said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.6"
msgid "“kissa, mahārāja, ārāmikakulaṃ bandhāpitan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Great king, why have you had the family of that monastery worker "
"imprisoned?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.7"
msgid ""
"“Tassa, bhante, ārāmikassa ghare suvaṇṇamālā abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā."
msgstr ""
"“Venerable, in the house of that monastery worker there was a beautiful "
"golden garland."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.8"
msgid "Natthi tādisā amhākampi antepure suvaṇṇamālā."
msgstr "Even the royal compound has nothing like it."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.9"
msgid "Kuto tassa duggatassa."
msgstr "So how did those poor people get it?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.10"
msgid "Nissaṃsayaṃ corikāya ābhatā”ti."
msgstr "No doubt it was taken by theft.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā pilindavaccho rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa "
"pāsādaṃ suvaṇṇanti adhimucci."
msgstr ""
"Pilindavaccha then focused his mind on turning King Bimbisāra’s stilt house "
"into gold."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.12"
msgid "So ahosi sabbasovaṇṇamayo."
msgstr "As a result the whole house became gold."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.13"
msgid "“Idaṃ pana te, mahārāja, tāva bahuṃ suvaṇṇaṃ kuto”ti?"
msgstr "And he said, “Great king, how did you get so much gold?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.14"
msgid "“Aññātaṃ, bhante, ayyasseveso iddhānubhāvo”ti."
msgstr "“Understood, Venerable, this is your supernormal power.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.15"
msgid "Taṃ ārāmikakulaṃ muñcāpesi."
msgstr "And he released that family."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-pli3.251, ms1V_2311
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.16"
msgid "Manussā—"
msgstr "People were saying,"

#. VAR: uttarimanussadhammaṃ → uttari­manus­sa­dhammā (bj)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.17"
msgid ""
"“ayyena kira pilindavacchena sarājikāya parisāya uttarimanussadhammaṃ "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassitan”ti,"
msgstr ""
"“It seems Venerable Pilindavaccha has performed a superhuman feat, a wonder "
"of supernormal power, for the king and his court!”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.18"
msgid ""
"attamanā abhippasannā āyasmato pilindavacchassa pañca bhesajjāni "
"abhihariṃsu, seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr ""
"Being delighted and gaining confidence in Pilindavaccha, they brought him "
"the five tonic:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.19"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ."
msgstr "ghee, butter, oil, honey, and sugar."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.20"
msgid "Pakatiyāpi ca āyasmā pilindavaccho lābhī hoti pañcannaṃ bhesajjānaṃ."
msgstr "Ordinarily, too, Pilindavaccha was getting these five tonics."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.21"
msgid "Laddhaṃ laddhaṃ parisāya vissajjeti."
msgstr "Since he was getting so much, he gave it away to his followers."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.22"
msgid "Parisā cassa hoti bāhullikā."
msgstr "As a consequence his followers acquired an abundance of tonics."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.23"
msgid ""
"Laddhaṃ laddhaṃ kolambepi ghaṭepi pūretvā paṭisāmeti, parissāvanānipi "
"thavikāyopi pūretvā vātapānesu laggeti."
msgstr ""
"After filling up jars and pitchers and setting these aside, they filled "
"their water filters and bags and hung these in the windows."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.131
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.24"
msgid "Tāni olīnavilīnāni tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr "The tonics were dripping all over"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.25"
msgid "Undūrehipi vihārā okiṇṇavikiṇṇā honti."
msgstr "and the dwellings became infested with rats."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.26"
msgid ""
"Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr ""
"When people who were walking about the dwellings saw this, they grumbled and "
"complained,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.27"
msgid ""
"“antokoṭṭhāgārikā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā, seyyathāpi rājā māgadho seniyo "
"bimbisāro”ti."
msgstr ""
"“These Sakyan ascetics are hoarding goods indoors, just like King Seniya "
"Bimbisāra of Magadha.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_2312
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.28"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.29"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.30"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.31"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū evarūpāya bāhullāya cetessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can these monks choose to live in such abundance?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2313
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.32"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ "
"ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.33"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū evarūpāya bāhullāya cetentī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks are living like this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.34"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.35"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.36"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā evarūpāya bāhullāya cetessanti."
msgstr "How can those foolish men choose to live in such abundance?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.37"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.38"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2314
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.39"
msgid ""
"“Yāni kho pana tāni gilānānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭisāyanīyāni bhesajjāni, "
"seyyathidaṃ—"
msgstr "‘After being received, the tonics allowable for sick monks—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.40"
msgid "sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ,"
msgstr "that is, ghee, butter, oil, honey, and sugar—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.41"
msgid "tāni paṭiggahetvā sattāhaparamaṃ sannidhikārakaṃ paribhuñjitabbāni."
msgstr "should be used from storage for at most seven days."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:1.3.42"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"If one uses them beyond that, one commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, pts-cs-bu-np23.2, ms1V_2315
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.1"
msgid "Yāni kho pana tāni gilānānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭisāyanīyāni bhesajjānīti"
msgstr "The tonics allowable for sick monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.2"
msgid "sappi nāma"
msgstr "Ghee:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. VAR: mahiṃsasappi → mahisasappi (bj, s1-3) | mahisaṃ vā sappi (pts1)
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.132,  
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.3"
msgid ""
"gosappi vā ajikāsappi vā mahiṃsasappi vā yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati tesaṃ sappi."
msgstr ""
"ghee from cows, ghee from goats, ghee from buffaloes, or ghee from whatever "
"animal whose meat is allowable."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.4"
msgid "Navanītaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Butter:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.5"
msgid "tesaṃyeva navanītaṃ."
msgstr "butter from the same animals."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.6"
msgid "Telaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Oil:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.7"
msgid "tilatelaṃ sāsapatelaṃ madhukatelaṃ eraṇḍatelaṃ vasātelaṃ."
msgstr ""
"sesame oil, mustard seed oil, honey tree oil, castor oil, oil from tallow."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.8"
msgid "Madhu nāma"
msgstr "Honey:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.9"
msgid "makkhikāmadhu."
msgstr "honey from bees."

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.10"
msgid "Phāṇitaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Sugar:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.11"
msgid "ucchumhā nibbattaṃ."
msgstr "from sugar cane."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2316
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.12"
msgid "Tāni paṭiggahetvā sattāhaparamaṃ sannidhikārakaṃ paribhuñjitabbānīti"
msgstr ""
"After being received […] should be used from storage for at most seven days:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.13"
msgid "sattāhaparamatā paribhuñjitabbāni."
msgstr "they are to be used for seven days at the maximum."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_2317
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.14"
msgid "Taṃ atikkāmayato nissaggiyaṃ hotīti"
msgstr ""
"If one uses them beyond that, one commits an offense entailing "
"relinquishment:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.15"
msgid "aṭṭhame aruṇuggamane nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "it becomes subject to relinquishment at dawn on the eighth day."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.16"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr ""
"The tonics should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.17"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, they should be relinquished in this way: …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.18"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr ""
"To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-"
"np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.19"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, bhesajjaṃ sattāhātikkantaṃ nissaggiyaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"‘Venerables, these tonics that I have kept over seven days are to be "
"relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.20"
msgid "imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish them to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.21"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.22"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.23"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give these tonics back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.23a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc12, pts-vp-pli3.252, ms1V_2318
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.24"
msgid "Sattāhātikkante atikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than seven days and he perceives it as more than seven days, "
"he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.25"
msgid "Sattāhātikkante vematiko, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than seven days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.26"
msgid "Sattāhātikkante anatikkantasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If it is more than seven days, but he perceives it as less than seven days, "
"he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.27"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been determined, but he perceives them as determined, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.28"
msgid "Avissajjite vissajjitasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been given away, but he perceives them as given away, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.29"
msgid "Anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been lost, but he perceives them as lost, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.30"
msgid "Avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been destroyed, but he perceives them as destroyed, he "
"commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.31"
msgid "Adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been burnt, but he perceives them as burnt, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.133
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.32"
msgid "Avilutte viluttasaññī, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"If they have not been stolen, but he perceives them as stolen, he commits an "
"offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2319
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.33"
msgid ""
"Nissaṭṭhaṃ paṭilabhitvā na kāyikena paribhogena paribhuñjitabbaṃ, na "
"ajjhoharitabbaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"After the relinquished tonics have been returned, they are not to be used on "
"the body, nor are they to be eaten."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.34"
msgid "padīpe vā kāḷavaṇṇe vā upanetabbaṃ,"
msgstr "They can used in lamps or as a black coloring agent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.35"
msgid ""
"aññena bhikkhunā kāyikena paribhogena paribhuñjitabbaṃ, na ajjhoharitabbaṃ."
msgstr "Other monks may use them on the body, but they may not eat them."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2320
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.36"
msgid "Sattāhānatikkante atikkantasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than seven days, but he perceives it as more than seven days, "
"he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.37"
msgid "Sattāhānatikkante vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than seven days, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.38"
msgid "Sattāhānatikkante anatikkantasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If it is less than seven days and he perceives it as less than seven days, "
"there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.38a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2321
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.39"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.40"
msgid ""
"antosattāhaṃ adhiṭṭheti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, "
"acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr ""
"if within seven days they have been determined, given away, lost, destroyed, "
"burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.41"
msgid ""
"anupasampannassa cattena vantena muttena anapekkho datvā paṭilabhitvā "
"paribhuñjati,"
msgstr ""
"if, without any desire for them, he gives them up to a person who is not "
"fully ordained, and he then obtains them again and then uses them;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.42"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.43"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc16, ms1V_2322
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np23:2.44"
msgid "Bhesajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ."
msgstr "The third rule, the training rule on tonics, is finished."
